annotationA: Clathrin-associated adaptor complex AP-1 medium chain; Clathrin binding; protein transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: vesicle coating; synaptic vesicle coating; negative regulation of Notch signaling pathway; vesicle-mediated transport; intracellular transport; negative regulation of endocytic recycling; compound eye development; secretory granule organization; intracellular protein transport; neurotransmitter secretion; Belongs to the adaptor complexes medium subunit family
annotationB: Adaptor Protein complex 2, sigma subunit is a component of the AP-2 adaptor complex, which recruits certain transmembrane proteins into clathrin-coated pits for endocytic internalization
